Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%can}. Finely dice the @red onion{1}(finely diced). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Dice the @zucchini{1}(diced into 1/2-inch cubes). Halve the @lemon{1}(halved).

Heat @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add the onion and cook, tossing, for about ~{5%minutes}, until softened. Add the @sugar snap peas{4%oz} and zucchini and cook until snap peas are crisp-tender and zucchini has softened, about ~{3-4%minutes}. Set aside.

In the same pan, add another @olive oil{2%tsp}. Season both sides of the @skin-on salmon{2}(skin on) with @salt{} and @pepper{} and add to the pan skin side-down first. Sear for about ~{2-3%minutes} per side until slightly opaque in the center. Add @butter{1%tbsp} to the pan and the juice of half the lemon. Spoon butter-lemon sauce over salmon. Set aside and cover with #foil.

In the same pan, add garlic and cook over medium heat for ~{30%seconds} before adding the @Dijon mustard{1%tsp} and @coriander{1%tsp}. Cook for ~{30%seconds}, then add the butter beans, onion, zucchini, and snap peas to the pan. Cook, tossing, for ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer for about ~{3%minutes}, until broth has slightly thickened.

Serve the salmon atop the butter bean and zucchini salad with a squeeze of lemon from the remaining half.